title: Greyhound field hockey’s comeback falls short in home finale
text:
PHOTOS BY BILL SLATTERY Kline 
Greyhound field hockey nearly came back from a 2-0 deficit thanks to hard work from the likes of Maddie Kline during their home finale against Big Spring. Frohm 
Senior Taylor Frohm battles Big Spring’s Leah Gutshall for possession Thursday. Posted: Tuesday, October 20, 2015 6:00 am Greyhound field hockey’s comeback falls short in home finale By ANDREW MILLER Sports Writer ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
Big Spring field hockey’s Kelly Shulenberger ran wild on the Shippensburg Greyhounds in the Greyhounds’ home finale Thursday.
